  "prompt": "How do I promote my music for free?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to promote your music for free:\n\n1. Social Media Platforms\n- Create artist pages on Facebook, Instagram, TikTok\n- Share music clips and behind-the-scenes content\n- Use relevant hashtags\n- Engage with fans and other musicians\n\n2. Music Streaming Services\n- Upload to Spotify, Apple Music, SoundCloud\n- Create playlists\n- Submit to user-curated playlists\n- Use Spotify for Artists features\n\n3. YouTube\n- Create a music channel\n- Upload music videos\n- Use SEO-friendly titles and descriptions\n- Collaborate with other creators\n\n4. Online Music Communities\n- Reddit music forums\n- ReverbNation\n- Bandcamp\n- Music blogs and forums\n\n5. Networking\n- Attend local music events\n- Connect with other musicians\n- Collaborate on projects\n\n6. Email Marketing\n- Build an email list\n- Send updates about new music\n- Share exclusive content\n\n7. Music Blogs and Podcasts\n- Submit music for potential reviews\n- Reach out to independent music blogs\n- Pitch to podcast playlists\n\n8. Live Streaming\n- Perform on Twitch\n- Use Instagram/Facebook Live\n- Host virtual concerts\n\n9. Music Submission Websites\n- Submit to playlist curators\n- Use free submission platforms\n\nRemember consistency and quality are key to building an audience.",
